      {
        "id": 19320511,
        "user_id": 1472254,
        "title": "IXPE Data Visualization ",
        "description": "This project utilizes data provided by NASA's IXPE Safelight, courtesy of LASP, to visualize the magnetic field of a neutron star. Houdini's VDB editing capabilities were employed to create a smoke field, while its interpolation tools were used to generate additional points based on the provided data. These points were integrated into the smoke field and simulation to achieve a comprehensive particle simulation that accurately reflects the data. Blender was then used for rendering, ensuring a high-quality visual representation of the results.\n\n",
